content: The ads in the free one weren't all that annoying, except for that one malicious one, but I thought the developer deserves at least 99 cents. The start up process could be a little more efficient but it's been keeping me entertained. (That there's an ad-free version in the first place adds to the almost flawless functionallity in making this app better than the Solitaire game I started out with when I first got my tablet.) Finally! I won three (random draw) games in a row. (And I've done that a "few" times since then.) The only thing "unrealistic" about the game is that computers generally do a much better job of randomly mixing cards than people. Keep the winter themes as an option when winter goes away. I'm seeing nothing at all "off" or weird about the card shuffling. I just won four random draw games in a row. Well, it's six in a row now. (The probability of winning a (hard) guaranteed winnable game is actually lower than that of winning a random deal one. The guaranteed winnable deals would be better if they weren't separated into difficulty levels. The difficulty level should be random.)
I paid for this and it has not been on my phone yet !!! What's up with that ? How do I get my money back ??!!
replyContent: If you have trouble downloading the app, please check there is enough free memory, restart the device or search for an error message if there is one. Sorry, download is managed by Google, not us, so we have no control over it but if you still can't get the app to install, please contact support@aifactory.co.uk for a refund.

I understand you might be a small company, but 5000-10000 sales surely merits a fix for these core functions? Far less important, but it would also be nice to allow quitting the app at the congratulations graphic.  Edit (after reply) You have 31 apps to look after and there hasn’t been an update for this one for nearly 8 months… even then it was a festive theme pack :/
replyContent: Thank you for your review. Difficulty levels are only a guide and different human play styles may find some cpu puzzle styles easier than others. We have added your other suggestions for consideration on our to-do list, however as we're a very small team with lots of apps to look after we can't say how long it might take to assess any work.
